luster_name\" : \"es-cluster\",\n  \"status\" : \"green\",\n  \"timed_out\" : false,\n  \"number_of_nodes\" : 3,\n  \"number_of_data_nodes\" : 3,\n  \"active_primary_shards\" : 3,\n  \"active_shards\" : 6,\n  \"relocating_shards\" : 1,\n  \"initializing_shards\" : 0,\n  \"unassigned_shards\" : 0,\n  \"delayed_unassigned_shards\" : 0,\n  \"number_of_pending_tasks\" : 1,\n  \"number_of_in_flight_fetch\" : 0,\n  \"task_max_waiting_in_queue_millis\" : 0,\n  \"active_shards_percent_as_number\" : 100.0\n}\n\n=== Nodes (master shown with *) ===\nip           heap.percent ram.percent cpu load_1m load_5m load_15m node.role master name\n10.244.0.105           59          62  53    5.87    7.48     8.82 dim       *      es-cluster-1\n10.244.0.106           47          56  99    5.87    7.48     8.82 dim       -      es-cluster-2\n10.244.0.104           49          61  32    5.87    7.48     8.82 dim       -      es-cluster-0\n\n=== Verify no initial_master_nodes in running config ===\ninitial_master_nodes not present in running config (correct)","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KeLAyQ5wYG6TgmeqFgEQ8j","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All goals achieved:\n\n**What was wrong:** The `es-config` ConfigMap was missing `cluster.initial_master_nodes`. Elasticsearch 7.x requires this setting to bootstrap a brand-new cluster — without it, nodes start but none can initiate a master election, so they all spin indefinitely with \"master not discovered yet.\"\n\n**What was done:**\n1. **Added `cluster.initial_master_nodes: [es-cluster-0, es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2]`** to the ConfigMap — this allowed the master election to proceed on restart.\n2. **Rolling restart (ordered, pod-by-pod)** — each pod restarted and came back ready before the next was touched, keeping the cluster available.\n3. **Cluster formed** (green, 3 nodes, master elected).\n4. **Removed `cluster.initial_master_nodes`** from the ConfigMap — this setting must not persist; if it remained, a future accidental re-bootstrap could split the cluster state.\n5. **Second rolling restart** — confirmed the cluster stays green and a master is re-elected without the bootstrap setting. The cluster state is now persisted on each node's data volume, so discovery works via `discovery.seed_hosts` alone on all future restarts.\n\n**Final state:** cluster `green`, 3/3 nodes ready, master on es-cluster-1, `cluster.initial_master_nodes` absent from both the ConfigMap and running node configuration."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":832,"cache_read_input_tokens":38612,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":832},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"af7010da-7e33-4625-ba40-ca5530d42cc2","uuid":"fad15d0b-bff1-47da-b0c9-d1dc09bd3b1f","request_id":"req_011CcQ9WhGDUHr23cGFkB5G6"}
